caption.text: My little boy, Haru. Here‚Äôs the story: I love small animals so much. When I came to Taiwan, I saw a lot of people raise a dog and toy-poodles stole my heart with their teddy-bear-look which I rarely saw in Indonesia. When I had to choose which one which I would like to bring home, there are a couple of red toy poodle and a couple of black toy poodle. Haru wasn‚Äôt like common toy-poodle; he has a red nose, not black. But far from their appearance, he is very charming and lovable. I had decided to adopt him and just tell my parent after I brought him home. I have been living with Haru almost for four years and he never fails me to make me love him. He grew up into a very smart boy which he learned so fast many tricks. But I‚Äôve decided to take him home first this November due to personal factors. I hope all the process goes well. caption.text: I was invited to new branch opening at well-known Manado restaurant in Jakarta, called Beautika. I've never heard about them before but never thought that related to traditional restaurant. So I asked the owner the story behind and found an interesting story. When Indonesian crisis economic around 90's, they started to open an aesthetic beauty salon in Jakarta. Since they lack of human resources, many customers were waiting to be treated and start to hungry. Then the owner serve them home-cooking foods for satisfy them. As the time goes by, many customers came to Beautika only for the food. Beautika has been opened for almost 20 years, and the time proved how they manage their restaurant seriously. If you like spicy dishes, these place is must try!

Appreciate what you have then life will be easier. üì∑ : @silas.aja

I'm a fussy freaks (baca: rempong). I spend times in front of laptop to research the destination spot before, including how to go, best spots, sightseeing spots nearby, and eat-out plan. I found that being organized is the way more efficient. But once, bf parked his new motorbike in front of my apartment, told me to get on and just follow him. I didn't have any idea where to go and he took me to the northern coast of Taiwan. He stopped in a unfamiliar ferry terminal and told me to get off. I kept asking where are we going while saw a bunch of people walk by on the same way. And here it is, he led me to the place I wanted to go for a long time. Bcause there's no public transport to reach here, I kept endured it and I didn't expect he took me there for real. Well, I'd enjoy this little surprises, that's so sweet of him üíô

caption.text:
My super dad teach me how to climb a dream as high as a mountain. 
We used to had arguments, quarrels, forgive and forgiven. We are too similar with each other so that we often have a fight. Sometimes I hate that my father has to much attention to his job. He often make me waiting due to his work, and I hate that. As I grew up, I didn't realize that the path I lead is more likely become like him. My father is the role model who I want to be. He is persistent and brave. He was an artist when he was young, he like to draw and play music. But my grandpa forbid him to learn architecture, so he learn civil engineering instead. As he graduated, he learn architecture by himself and make him become who he is now. He build his own name by seek for customers, sketching, order the materials, and build the constructions. I'm a proud daughter when I say first Java Dancer cafe and reconstruction Klub Bunga have been built by my dad. Although he perhaps didn't aware today's celebration and I'm away from him just right now. I just wanna say I love you, dad. I know that you care about me even you didn't mention it. Happy 88's day for those super dad!

I spent a half hour queueing for 5 buns. Speaking of Taiwan culture: Queueing too much? 
Well, I've been here almost six years long. I'm pretty familiar to Taiwanese culture and somehow I accidentally take it as habit now. Culture shock is very common when you decide to settle down in another country. Generally speaking, Taiwanese is so polite and honest. Once, I found my wallet missing after I got down from taxi, too many valuable cards inside that made me so anxious. I gave up and surrendered because no matter I looked for, just useless. Then suddenly an unknown caller ID appeared on my phone, he said someone find my wallet and hand over to security service. And countless times when I walked on the street, Taiwanese usually remind me to pull zipper bag closed. But somehow always keep me wondering is, why Taiwanese love to queue? No jokes, they could queue at least one hour and more for buy something, and no one dare to jump into the line. Then, after six years of observation I finally understand why. They queue to express appreciation of sth. Time which they spent denotes how much they put value into it. Not only for buying sth, Taiwanese also have integrity to appreciate arts. I think these something that we should learn from them, even we couldn't change our culture but at least we start from ourselves, right?  #vscotaiwan #spottly

caption.text:
Ok, this my turn after nominated by @youween @henryjonathann @clemencyyoan @chalophjesus It's still little bit awkward for me. Here it is #20factsaboutme :
1.I have been staying in Taiwan for almost 4 year and still counting.
2.Because I took a year of foundation, I started my degree late. But, at last, I will take another year to obtain my master degree.
3.I enjoy taking pictures and retouch them. You won't find music or games applications on my iphone, I only have editing apps.
4.I always drink 800ml of water once I wake up in the morning. Hence, I bring my bottle wherever I go.
5.Haru is a part of me. He is a cute-smart-red-nose toy poodle.
6.I believe that chance will come only once in your life.
7.I don't occasionally hang out and eating good food everyday. My Instagram blinds you over. 
8.I put make up whenever I need to be more confidence in front of certain people.
9.I'm the shortest among my family, including my little sister.
10.Honestly, i'm kind of sentimental person.
11.I worked as a part-timer 7 times and I traveled aboard using the money I got from those jobs.
12.I do silly things and be super talk active in front of my best friends. But, I will be way calmer in front of strangers.
13.I was born on 20th of May (520) which means ÊàëÊÑõ‰Ω†(wo ai ni=i love you) in chinese.
14.Even tough I clearly know that my passion and talent is in Design. I never regret being a business student instead.
15.I love bread, milk, and cheese. Therefore my cholesterol is out of normal now.
16.I put my family above everything else.
17.I do have haters, but i concerned about people who love me most.
18.There will be a time when I'll build and manage my own cafe.
19.I My english is getting worse while my chinese is getting better, much better actually.
20.I can't tolerate ANY kind of spicy food. Sorry to say, I dislike them.
